Job Description:
Under direct supervision of Head of Business Development Department, Leasing Specialist is responsible for planning and directing general leasing activities, reviewing and monitoring leasing products and offering leasing policies and procedures training to relevant staff as well as ensures sales target is achieved with high portfolio quality. Also, Leasing Specialist will be responsible for developing new leasing products and build partnership with stakeholders and technical institutions. S/he will also ensure good customer service, and high client retention rate.

Duties and Responsibilities

Leasing Product Planning and Management:

- Assist with annual planning for leasing activities and distribution of leasing services to clients and help to set target plan of leasing portfolio and clients;
- Recommend revisions of policies, procedures and evaluation process of finance lease;
- Develop and/or revise forms for finance lease product of TPC;
- Develop materials and plan for training and conduct training on finance lease policy, procedure, forms, evaluation process, finance lease products and credit risk management to finance lease responsible officers and Branch Management;
- Lead and coach finance lease responsible officers in coordination with branch and management to assess the cash flow and risks of all types of businesses during inputs, production process, work in process, and outputs etc.; and
- Coordinate events and the training programs in partnership with strategic service providers.

Leasing Product Monitoring and Reporting

- Visit branches regularly to evaluate credit officers’ finance lease evaluation skills;
- Take immediate actions to improve all weaknesses of finance lease responsible officers and other relevant staff and management of the branch;
- Set up a standard monitoring system to strengthen and improve the performance of finance lease responsible officers and other relevant staff;
- Prepare periodic reports and maintains appropriate files and records for finance lease activities and training for staff and clients;
- Monitor and evaluate risks associated with finance lease and recommended mitigation strategies to Senior Management;
- Regularly report in written and verbally to Supervisor and/or Senior Management.

Finance Lease Product Development and Relationship Building:

- Understand value chain and supply chain activities for finance lease products and incorporate knowledge into risk management strategies and development of new products;
- Conduct market research and propose new finance lease products that will address more effectively clients’ needs and contribute to the profitability of TPC clients and TPC operation;
- Work closely with other non-profit organizations, companies, authorized dealers/ suppliers and other technical institutions on possible partnerships especially in seeking for relevant trainings on finance lease products for all finance lease responsible officers and supervisors;
- Build strong relationship with local authorities aimed at regularly gathering and updating information exchange on business sector situation in Cambodia; and
- Maintain a library of information and materials related to all kinds of business activities in Cambodia and neighboring countries; keep the information and materials up to date.

Motivation & Mentoring activities:

- Motivate and mentor all subordinates, especially finance lease responsible officers and relevant branches that are handling finance lease accounts;
- Be opened-minded and responsive and welcome all comments and feedback from all staff and management of branches and head office;
- Professionally and personally advise and give proper solutions to any problem of any staff;
- Have good communication and build close relation with all staff under supervision;
- Promote a team work spirit; and
- Recommend a rewarding system of finance lease responsible officers specializing in finance lease to Senior Management for consideration.

Job Requirement:
- Experience in finance lease companies, microfinance institutions, rural-oriented banks, or related experiences, preferably in handling finance lease;
- At least a bachelor degree in finance & banking, business administration or any other related field;
- Demonstrated strategic and creative thinking abilities;
- Sense of ownership of assigned projects and associated results. Ability to manage multiple high priority projects and work effectively both as an individual and as part of a team; 
- Familiar with survey methodologies and techniques on all kinds of businesses & trade & commerce and service;
